debugger-instrumentation — Phase 1: poll points, breakpoints, two-thread pause
===============================================================================

See also:
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-implementation-plan.org (Phase 1)
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-spec.org (§5.3, §6, §11, §12)
  issues/open/debugger-source-map.issue (prerequisite — Phase 0)

Context
-------

With the form-id source map in place (Phase 0), v1 instrumentation pulls the
spec §5 two-bodies (Raskin) discipline forward INTO the interpreter rather
than using the §11.3 evaluator-flag variant. Each instrumentable
`autolisp-usubr` carries two bodies: the plain `body` (always) and an
`instrumented-body` (only when instrumented). The ordinary body has no
poll-point nodes, so un-debugged execution costs zero — not even a per-form
flag check. See the plan's §3a for the full rationale and the comparison
with §11.3. The compiler emitting two CL bodies (§5.1) stays deferred to
Phase 8; this is its AST-level analog.

Scope / deliverables
--------------------

1. New system `clautolisp/autolisp-debug` (depends on bordeaux-threads).

2. Instrumentation pass + two-body dispatch (plan §3a):
   - Add `instrumented-body` (+ `debug-metadata`) slots to `autolisp-usubr`.
   - Weave `%poll k :before` / `:after` nodes around every sub-form and
     function enter/exit nodes (spec §5.3 shape) into a COPY of `body`,
     producing `instrumented-body`; `%poll` is a debug special operator.
     Builtin `autolisp-subr`s are opaque — never instrumented (stepped over).
   - At the apply boundary, `call-autolisp-function-in-context` selects
     `instrumented-body` vs `body` via a dynamic `*debugging*` indicator
     (Fjeld propagation, robust to REPL redefinition; checked at call sites
     only, not per sub-form). Un-instrumented callees fall back to `body`
     (= step-over, matching the remote REQ-LOAD2 rule).

3. `poll-point` hot path (spec §11.1): debug-flag fast path -> 1024-bit
   Bloom test -> exact breakpoint lookup -> `handle-breakpoint`. Hot path
   must be allocation-free; combine (function, form-id) into a fixnum hash
   inline or use a two-level table.

4. Breakpoint API (spec §12): `add-breakpoint` / `remove-breakpoint` /
   `list-breakpoints`; steady vs volatile; set Bloom bit on add, lazy
   rebuild on shrink (false positives tolerated, false negatives not).

5. Two-thread pause (spec §8.2/§8.3): application thread enqueues `:hit` on
   its outbound queue and blocks on its inbound queue; the debugger thread
   drives it; `:continue` resumes. bordeaux-threads blocking queue + semaphore.

Acceptance
----------

- A steady breakpoint set on a form in a loaded .lsp stops execution at that
  form; `:continue` resumes; a second hit works.
- Bloom filter demonstrably skips the overwhelming majority of non-breakpoint
  poll points (microbenchmark or counter).
- FiveAM tests; `*version*` bumped.
